5% chance of ingestion during a kiss gives a 95% chance of it, you know, not happening. 95% can also be written as 0.95 (since it's 95 parts out of 100). If you want to know the chance of something happening more than once, you simply multiply it with itself: 0.95 * 0.95 = 0,9025. Meaning there's a ~90% chance of not having been ingested after two kisses. Keep multiplying it with 0.95 (since that's still the chance of it not happening during any one kiss) and you get ~77% after 5 kisses, ~60% after 10, and so on

Well, you can find someone to talk with, I'm sure. There are some Anons here who are easy to get ahold of, and there are /trash/ generals essentially just for that, too.
>>34717830
That isn't always the case - it's not bad advice necessarily, but that is just simply no catch-all solution to social isolation (self-afflicted or circumstantial). I can't speak for everyone, but believe me, there are things that are easier spoken in confidence with a friend than with the family who are around you every day. Maybe it's an age-to-available-friends thing that just makes it harder the older you get; we all have reasons for the facades we put forth with those closest to us, so family isn't an option for some.
A complete shift in character and presentation may help someone with some as-yet repressed social skill make friends in real irl life, making that the soundest solution for those of us with the determination to effect real and meaningful change in our lives. However, lacking that, someone leaning closer toward "absolute lonerdom" on the social golden mean scale (as is the case with most here, more than should otherwise be normal) will understandably struggle more with that than others in part because they're the sort of people who NEED those connections to help motivate them. I like the analogies we have available to us here and nowhere else - some Anons (or waifurs if I'm writing) really are just at the precipice of living where literally (sic) the presence of just one person can be the difference between bravely putzing around that sheer drop in painful isolation, or giving in to the bullshit life keeps throwing at them and taking that desperate plunge into sweet oblivion.
